<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1094,283,345]" box="[264,422,319,345]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,413,319,345]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="26.[264,382,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[394,1196,616,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-202@26.[387,1200,604,1441]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Chrysotimus xiaohuangshanus sp. nov. (male). 52. Wing; 53. first flagellomere, lateral view; 54. genitalia, laterial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048695/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Figs. 52–54</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1320,399,545]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis. Six dc, 6–7 irregularly paired acr. Fore and mid tarsomere 1 each with row of 5–6 v; hind tarsomere 1 with about 20 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/5 and row of 7–8 pv. Epandrium apically with long and broad process.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1320,399,545]" box="[312,1040,518,545]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,533,518,544]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[692,785,519,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[943,1036,519,545]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048695" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048695/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" startId="26.[264,382,1467,1491]" targetBox="[394,1196,616,1435]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,1467,1525]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,463,1467,1491]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">FIGURES 52–54.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[470,798,1468,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaohuangshanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[470,798,1468,1491]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Chrysotimus xiaohuangshanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[805,888,1468,1491]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 52. Wing; 53. first flagellomere, lateral view; 54. genitalia, laterial view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,1577,1883]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head brown. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1142,1657,1683]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="26.[264,382,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[394,1196,616,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-202@26.[387,1200,604,1441]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Chrysotimus xiaohuangshanus sp. nov. (male). 52. Wing; 53. first flagellomere, lateral view; 54. genitalia, laterial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048695/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 0.7 times as long as wide; arista dorsal, with basal segment very short. Proboscis brown, with yellow hairs; palpus yellow, with yellow hairs and 2 yellow apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[264,1323,1577,1883]" lastBlockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 6 strong dc, 6–7 irregularly paired acr short and hair­like; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 pale short bristle on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; fore and mid coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 2–3 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 1–2 anterior bristles, hind coxa with 1 brownish outer bristle near middle. Fore femur with 1 short pv apically; mid femur with 1 av apically; hind femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad, 2 pd, and 1 pv, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore and mid tarsomere 1 each with row of 5–6 yellow v; hind tarsomere 1 with about 20 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/5, and row of 7–8 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 3.2: 2.0: 0.9: 0.7: 0.5: 0.5; LII 4.2: 2.7: 1.1: 0.8: 0.5: 0.5; LIII 5.3: 2.3: 1.4: 1.0: 0.6: 0.5.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation box="[484,571,684,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="26.[264,382,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[394,1196,616,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-202@26.[387,1200,604,1441]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Chrysotimus xiaohuangshanus sp. nov. (male). 52. Wing; 53. first flagellomere, lateral view; 54. genitalia, laterial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048695/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[803,839,695,716]" fontSize="9" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.28. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen brownish.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[504,596,849,875]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="26.[264,382,1467,1491]" captionTargetBox="[394,1196,616,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-202@26.[387,1200,604,1441]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Chrysotimus xiaohuangshanus sp. nov. (male). 52. Wing; 53. first flagellomere, lateral view; 54. genitalia, laterial view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048695/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Epandrium about as long as wide, apically with long and broad lateral process, which bearing 4 spine­like apical bristles; surstylus broad, with obtuse process at corner, apically with 3 bristles; cercus round with somewhat acute apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" box="[312,536,969,995]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
