<paragraph blockId="27.[264,1325,284,1395]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Comments. This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang and Saigusa" authorityName="Yang and Saigusa" box="[804,1258,1169,1195]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[804,1043,1169,1194]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Chrysotimus setosus</emphasis>
Yang and Saigusa
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[264,361,1209,1235]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, but may be separated from the latter by fore and mid tarsomere 1 each with row of 5–6 v, and epandrium basally with long and broad process. In 
<taxonomicName box="[1043,1163,1249,1275]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setosus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1062,1249,1274]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1078,1163,1249,1274]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">setosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the fore and mid tarsomere 1 each has no distinct v, and the epandrium has short apical process (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T." pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="740 - 765" refId="ref12105" refString="Yang, D. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2005) Diptera: Dolichopodidae. In: Yang, X. (Ed.), Insect Fauna of Middle-West Qinling Range and South Mountains of Gansu Province. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 740 - 765." type="book chapter" year="2005">Yang and Saigusa, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
